node.title: Victoria records 1,419 new COVID-19 cases and 10 deaths
node.description: There are now 12,728 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 527 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,419\u00a0new\u00a0COVID-19 cases and 10\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 12,728\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 527\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "The health department yesterday removed a duplicate death from previous reporting.", "There are now 288\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 41\u00a0are in intensive care and 20\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 50\u00a0people were in intensive care but their infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 70,343\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 4,019\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
Heavily mutated Omicron variant puts scientist on alert
"]
